text:
hammer is a super fun weapon to play, and not too complicated for beginners, im glad to see you enjoying it!

you mentioned gunlance, and as a gunlance main i'll give you my 2 cents. first, despite the name, its NOT a ranged weapon. its basically a lance with a shotgun strapped on. combo mellee slaps with shells, that ignore armour and weakspot stuff so do set damage.

its a somewhat complex weapon, but not as bad as a chargeblade. it has things called 'shelling type', either normal type, wide type or long type. and you play the weapon differently based on each type. normal is probably the toughest because it has massive wind-up on its combo, similar to chargeblade SAED. you do mellee combos then after the downwards slam press the shot button to unload the whole clip into them, called a 'full burst'

the other two types are much simpler but im less experienced in them in this game. wide type combines pokes with standard shell shots and a special mini-finisher called wyvernstake where you stab it with a stake that then explodes. it also does stun damage with wide type shelling! long type is nearly entirely just shelling, but you hold the button to charge the shells. shots are slower but do more damage. it also lets you go into your block much faster then the other styles after attacking so its pretty safe.

then theres the switch skills. theres a bunch but the two that are worth remembering are charged slash, where you drag the weapon along the ground (and you can actually smack the monster while doing it, with hyper armour!) and this buffs your shots by 20% for a little while. the other is a guard point reload. basically a 'counter' that lets you reload your shells while blocking. 

the absolute greatest switch skill in the game is only really useful with normal type but is SO FUN. blast dash. you lose the ability to charge shells, but instead put the weapon behind you and yeet yourself through the air! its a great closer and you can even use it to travel around the map, using it up to 3 times in a row before you land, even changing direction each time. ive travelled across half the map with it before!

text:
its a good thing to try more than one weapon, a new weapon can change the game play and mix things up, its pretty fun to try a quick fast one, then also give a slow heavy hitter  a try. You can also find which playstyle you like the most. I used to play greatsword only, then I tried other weapons, ended up a switch axe main after, cuz the combos are so cool.

hammer tips:

if the monster is near, you can move by charging the hammer. It buffs the movespeed of the drawn weapon and the next attack that comes is stronger. It maybe better to sheathe and run to the monster if its not that near.

the length of the charge yields three moves, charge one is a combo extender, its just more hits, you can go to XXX after. Charge 2 has massive stun damage but low actual damage. Charge three is burst damage. 3 changes if you are moving ( spin, which can be ended early w X so no big delay on last hit) or a smash, if you are standing still. The hammer also has another charge mode, blue hammer. The moves look a little different but more or less function similar. combo extend, stun and burst. Blue set is a little stronger.

XXX is a bread and butter combo, easy triple hit w good damage.
AAAAA is a combo vs a monster that isnt able to move or is busy w somthing. The combo is stopped with huge lag if one strike misses, leaving you open. It does insane damage if it all hits. 

hammer strikes proc exhaust. It creates a drooling tired animation and a special stagger. You can beat it up more when this happens. Hammer head shots also proc stun. The monster gets knocked out and you can beat it up more. ideally you stick to the head and keep hitting it. The more you cause these effects to happen, the harder it will be to reapply it.
